    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment concludes that the FEA modeling framework is sufficiently credible for the intended COU. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved level 1 versus required level 2) is accepted given that ASTM F1717 single-condition testing is the established regulatory standard and the model is not being used to extrapolate beyond this condition. All three QoIs satisfy pre-specified quantitative acceptance criteria with E/uval values well below 1.96. The ensemble of three independent FEA implementations provides additional confidence in the predictions. The package is accepted as sufficient to support the 510(k) submission.",
